    Meet Mark Loveless

    The Creator of Loveless Pottery

     

    Mark Loveless graduated from Mount Rainier Lutheran High School Spring of 2013. While attending Mount Rainier, he spent three years under the mentorship of Kurt Scearce, head of the art department, and spent over 2000 hours in front of a pottery wheel.  Over these three years he developed many unique skills that make him the potter he is today.

     

    Mark is a young and upcoming entrepreneur in the art world. But like many aspiring artists, it took dedication, perseverance, and a lot of clay under his nails to get where he is today. 

     

    "After you have looked at the pots I created, it may be hard for you to believe that pottery did not come naturally to me! In fact it took over 1000 hours of practice before I could consistently create a simple bowl. Despite the difficulty of creating pots, I continued to practice and have collectively spent over 6000 hours in front of a pottery wheel. I still have much to learn, but I can testify to the positive results of hard work, and dedication to doing what I love." -Mark Loveless
